<seg id=1> America admitted that a few hundred Iraqi civilians were killed in the air raid, and an English news reporter said that it's definitely not a military target. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Washington, 13 February. On 13 February, American White House admitted that a few hundred Iraqi civilians were killed in the air raid against Baghdad, the capital of Iraq, but they insisted that the multicountry troops were attacking a military target. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Fitzwolt, the White House spokesman, said that American government believed that it's a "real tragedy". </seg>
<seg id=4> However, he condemned President Sudam for arranging the civilians into the military facilities, and put them into danger. </seg>
<seg id=5> He said that America believed that the target was a control center of Iraqi troops. </seg>
<seg id=6> After painted and disguised to avoid reconnaissance, it's proved to be a military target. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> According to Xinhua News Agency, London, 13 February, Paul, the BBC journalist to Baghdad, the capital of Iraq, proved that there was no sign showing that the air-raid shelter in Baghdad, which was destroyed by the American bombers, was an Iraqi military disguise. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Paul made his speech on BBC TV news report. He refuted the American declaration that the air-raid shelter was a military disguise. </seg>
<seg id=9> Paul had been to the site of the bombed air-raid shelter, and there were about 400 civilians died. </seg>
</p>
